text: Whidbey Island (historical spellings Whidby, Whitbey, or Whitby) is the largest of the islands making up Island County, Washington, in the United States. Whidbey is about north of Seattle, and lies between the Olympic Peninsula and the I-5. It is home to Naval Air Station Whidbey Island. Whidbey Island is home to around 66,000 residents (according to the 2020 census). ==References== Category:Islands of the United States Category:Settlements in Washington (state)
